hooks.prompt:
A git commit is about to run in the ShopStack repo. Review the staged changes by running `git diff --cached` (and `git diff` for any unstaged context), applying the standards in .claude/agents/code-change-reviewer.md (multi-tenancy safety, structure, PEP8, docstyle, import order, flake8) and discussing test scenarios. Then return your decision as JSON on stdout in this exact shape — and nothing else after the JSON:

If the verdict is CHANGES_REQUIRED, output:
{"hookSpecificOutput":{"hookEventName":"PreToolUse","permissionDecision":"deny","permissionDecisionReason":"<one-paragraph summary of blockers + actionable fixes>"}}

Otherwise (APPROVED or APPROVED_WITH_NITS), output:
{"hookSpecificOutput":{"hookEventName":"PreToolUse","permissionDecision":"allow"},"systemMessage":"<one-line review summary, including any nits or required follow-up tests>"}

Tool input that triggered this hook: $ARGUMENTS
